EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to offenders; authorizing the Director of the
Department of Corrections to establish a transitional
housing program for certain offenders to develop skills
and training relating to forestry management and
conservation; requiring the State Forester Firewarden to
establish a hiring program to appoint certain former
offenders to firefighting positions; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, the Director of the Department of Corrections is authorized
2 to enter into one or more contracts with one or more public or private entities to
3 provide certain services to offenders, including transitional housing. (NRS
4 209.4889) Section 4.5 of this bill authorizes the Director to establish, in
5 coordination with the Division of Forestry of the State Department of Conservation
6 and Natural Resources, a transitional housing program to provide training in
7 forestry management and conservation for certain offenders who: (1) are committed
8 to the custody of the Department and eligible for assignment to an institution or
9 facility of minimum security; and (2) have previously been denied parole solely due
10 to a lack of other available transitional housing.
11 Under existing law, the State Forester Firewarden, in cooperation with the
12 Department of Corrections, is required to establish and carry out a program for
13 operating conservation camps in this State which may use offenders who meet
14 certain requirements to perform certain work, including firefighting. (NRS
15 209.457) Section 5 of this bill requires the State Forester Firewarden to establish a
16 hiring program to appoint former offenders who performed firefighting work in
17 such conservation camps to firefighting positions in the Division of Forestry of the
18 State Department of Conservation and Natural Resources.
