5 Sec. 4.5. Chapter 209 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
6 thereto a new section to read as follows:
7 The Director may establish, in coordination with the Division
8 of Forestry of the State Department of Conservation and Natural
9 Resources, a transitional housing program to provide training in
10 forestry management and conservation for offenders who:
11 1. Are committed to the custody of the Department and
12 eligible for assignment to an institution or facility of minimum
13 security pursuant to the provisions of NRS 209.481; and
14 2. Have previously been denied parole solely due to a lack of
15 other available transitional housing.
16 Sec. 5. Chapter 472 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
17 thereto a new section to read as follows:
18 1. The State Forester Firewarden shall establish a hiring
19 program to provide a pathway to hire for firefighting positions
20 within this State. Under the hiring program, the State Forester
21 Firewarden may appoint a person to fill a position in the classified
22 service as a firefighter with the Division of Forestry of the State
23 Department of Conservation and Natural Resources if the person:
24 (a) Was a former offender assigned to work in a program for
25 operating conservation camps established pursuant to NRS
26 209.457 and performed work relating to firefighting;
27 (b) Successfully completed the training necessary to prepare
28 the offenders assigned to the conservation camp to assist in
29 firefighting pursuant to NRS 209.457;
30 (c) Has obtained any certifications required for employment as
31 a firefighter with the Division of Forestry; and
32 (d) Meets any other qualifications established by the State
33 Forester Firewarden.
34 2. The State Forester Firewarden may adopt regulations to
35 carry out the provisions of this section.
